<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-30T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="143" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d143">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A3/1864: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)<note n="47" xml:id="d143fn47">The same to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom
                                as Department’s telegram No. 461.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-30T14:00:00-05:00">December
                                    30, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>166. The Japanese Ambassador notified us on December 29 [<hi rend="italic">28</hi>] of the formal invocation by His Government of
                            Article 21 in order to retain 15,598 tons of excess submarines.</p>
                        <p>We have replied by note<note n="48" xml:id="d143fn48">
                                <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> that we will exercise our right
                            to retain a proportionate amount of tonnage in the submarine category
                            and on December 31, 1936, will have 15,230 tons of excess
                            submarines.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>